# payloadcms.ai — "Talk to your CMS"

## Product
AI interface for PayloadCMS: create content, update content, upload media, query CMS.
Target: developers, freelancers, agencies.

## Monorepo Layout
```
/apps/web        → Next.js (landing + app)
/apps/api        → NestJS (hexagonal architecture)
/packages/core   → domain types (intents, actions, tasks, plans)
/packages/agents → DAG + recursive agent system
/packages/events → typed event bus
/packages/adapters → CMS integrations (PayloadCMS)
/packages/billing → Stripe subscription logic
/packages/specs  → ALL specs (source of truth)
/packages/utils  → shared utilities
/tooling/cursor  → rules / commands / agents
```

## Philosophy
- Build minimal → validate → expand
- NEVER overbuild
- SPEED > PERFECTION, but STRUCTURE MUST HOLD
- Specs in `/packages/specs` are the ONLY source of truth
- ALL planning goes to spec files, never "plan mode"
- Charge early, validate willingness to pay

## Stack
- TypeScript strict everywhere
- pnpm workspaces + Turborepo
- Next.js (app router) for web
- NestJS (hexagonal) for API
- Stripe for billing
- OpenAI/Anthropic for LLM
